description:
&lt;p&gt;We are holding an assessment day for Band 2 support workers who are enthusiastic, motivated and committed to join our friendly team within the Emergency care &amp; Trauma.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with the Emergency care &amp; Trauma nursing team the post holder will become a member of the department who implements prescribed care and undertakes administrative activities as directed by a registered nurse and senior nursing team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be expected to provide direct technical assistance to registered nursing staff when required, safely, utilising electronic and mechanical/ manual equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to undertake and record clinical activities and observations, such as obtain specimens following training and assessment, as directed by the Registered Nurse. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will have:&lt;br /&gt;• GCSE or NVQ level 2&lt;br /&gt;• Proven written communication in their application&lt;br /&gt;• The ability to adapt to different hospital and satellite units as you may be required to work across various Barts Health sites&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shafina Yousuff, Senior Nurse, on 02035940684 or via shafina.yousuff@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
